{
  "stem": "21349.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And besides this, Germany is known for antisemitism, probably the root of antisemitism.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we was right, because 10 years later, they took away all citizenships, even from those who were born in Germany.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And if you're born in Germany, you don't become a German citizen by that anyhow.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My Father was not a citizen at all.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because he was born in Russia, in Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And near Kiev, Kharkov.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when he came over, he was a Russian citizen.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "However, when the Russian empire-- call it-- became Communist, Soviet-- Soviet-- Socialist Republic in 1922, '23, the Lenin, at that time, made a law that whoever wants to remain a Russian citizen must come here within three months, for a short period of time.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But my father didn't want to go back.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so all those who didn't go back, became stateless.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we were stateless, staatenlos.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Nuremberg laws were passed in 1935, and [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] it didn't change too much from what it was before.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because we knew already what was going to happen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] of course, the antisemitism got worse.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And people started to openly accuse accuse the Jews and-- kept away from them much more than ever before.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
